member.summary:
Logging class which logs messages through the ILoggingProvider interface.
By default it will use itself to log via the console and so you can simply call Logger.Log(...) and it will do its stuff. To change the logger you must call Logger.Logger = new some_implementation_of_ILoggingProvider() somewhere in your required application!
I suggest sticking this in your using!; using Logger = Moonrise.Utils.Standard.Logging.Logger;

All messages of Trace and higher (, , ,
,
) will be output

Starts a new nested scoped log tag.


    Usage:



    using (Logger.ScopedLogTag()){code} or Logger.ScopedLogTag("whatever"){code}
